.TH "@PACKAGE_NAME@" 1 "April, 2008", "@PACKAGE_VERSION@" "USER COMMANDS"
.SH NAME
@PACKAGE_NAME@ \- detaches a process from the terminal
.SH SYNOPSIS
.BR "@PACKAGE_NAME@ " "[OPTION] program [ARGUMENTS]"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B @PACKAGE_NAME@
Runs the specified program and detaches it from the terminal
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-c, --clear
Clears all the environment variables before executing the program
.TP
.B \-h, --help
Displays usage information
.TP
.B \-l, --log
Specifies a log file
.TP
.B \--version
prints the version of the program
.SH EXAMPLE
daemonizer --log /var/log/daemonizer.log -- deamon --option argument

Starts deamon with the --option option and argument and detaches it
from the terminal.
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
@PACKAGE_NAME@ returns a zero exist status if no errors occurred
